text: Alfred Teinitzer (29 July 1929 - 20 April 2021) was an Austrian footballer. He played as a midfielder. Teinitzer was born in Vienna. He played club football for Rapid Wien and LASK Linz. He also played for the Austria national team. He was part of the squad that finished third in the 1954 FIFA World Cup. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1929 births Category:2021 deaths Category:1954 FIFA World Cup players Category:Austrian footballers Category:Sportspeople from Vienna Category:LASK players Category:Austrian football midfielders
